[{"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Oberfinanzdirektion K\u00f6lnS-2230 - 55 - St 113S-2230 -EStG: 4 / 1EStG: 4 / 3EStG: 13a Income tax assessment of farmers and foresters for the assessment period 19831a) Maximum permitted number of animals in livestock units (VE) according to \u00a7 13a Paragraph 1 No. 3 EStG and \u00a7 13 Paragraph 1 No. 1 EStG (see Section 2) b) Animal husbandry settled with the starting amount (Section 521) in VE with an estimate of the profit according to standard rates (Section 5232) 2 examples for calculating the value of work (Section 13a Paragraph 5 EStG) 1 The assessment decisions for farmers and foresters will be published in full in future"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Changes to the text below are indicated by vertical lines"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "2 Determination of the profit from agriculture and forestry according to average rates (\u00a7 13a EStG) 21 Scope of application Supplementary to Section 127 Paragraphs 3 - 10 EStR and No. 2 of the introductory letter of the Federal Ministry of Finance of 27 03 1981 (BStBl 1981 I p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "282) the following is pointed out: 211 Regarding Section 13a Paragraph 1 No. 2 EStG (initial value limit) The initial value determined in accordance with Section 13a Paragraph 4 EStG is decisive"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Cattle surcharges can therefore not be taken into account as long as they have not been made the subject of a value update by the valuation body in accordance with \u00a7\u00a7 41 in conjunction with 22 para. 1 no. 1 BewG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Something else only applies if the requirements of Section 13a Paragraph 4 No. 1 Sentence 4 EStG are met"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "212 On Section 13a Paragraph 1 No. 3 EStG (animal population limit) According to Section 127 Paragraph 7 EStR and No. 22 of the introductory letter of 27 03 1981 a"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": ", is to be applied accordingly when examining the VE limits of Section 13a Paragraph 1 No. 3 EStG Section 124a EStR"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "The prerequisite for the elimination of the calculation of the average rate of profit is that the number of VE sustainably exceeds the limits of Section 13a (1) No. 3 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "For the term sustainability, reference is made to Section 135 (4) EStR"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "In the case of a gradual increase in the number of animals, it therefore depends on whether the number of animals converted into VE has been above the limits of Section 13a (1) No. 3 EStG over the three preceding financial years"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "If, as determined by the tax office, the number of animals has exceeded the maximum permitted limits in three consecutive financial years, the requirements of Section 13a (1) No. 3 EStG are no longer met from the beginning of the fourth financial year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "If, on the other hand, the livestock are increased in one go well beyond the maximum permissible limits - e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "in connection with an expansion of the stable capacities - so that the livestock limits can also be expected in the following financial years, the requirements of Section 13a (1) No. 3 EStG do not apply from the time the maximum limits are exceeded for the first time"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "The maximum number of animals permitted in accordance with Section 13a Paragraph 1 No. 3 and Section 13 Paragraph 1 No. 1 EStG, converted into VE, can be found in the overview attached as Annex 1"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "22 Determination of profit The scheme for determining profit according to \u00a7 13a Paragraph 3 to 8 EStG results from the form Annex ESt 2 L (80) - Profit determination according to \u00a7 13a EStG -"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "In detail, I would like to point out the following: 221 Basic amount When determining the basic amount according to Section 13a Paragraph 4 EStG, Section 130a Paragraph 3 EStR must be observed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "222 Value of the work performance In the case of the basic amount according to Section 13a (4) EStG, it is assumed that the business is managed exclusively with paid workers (see Section 36 (2) BewG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "The value of the work performed by the business owner and his relatives who are not employed in the company on the basis of an employment relationship to be determined in accordance with Section 13a (5) EStG must therefore be added to the basic amount (Section 13a (3) No. 2 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Section 130a, Paragraphs 4 to 6 EStR must be observed here"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "In detail, the following is pointed out: When determining the value of the work performance for the physical cooperation of the business owner and the relatives who are not employed, only the work performance is to be taken into account in the result, which is based on the area recorded in the initial value according to \u00a7 13a Paragraph 4 EStG in the individual case not applicable"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "The paid workers are to be counted towards the appropriate number of full-time workers (VAK) according to the duration of their employment (\u00a7 13a Abs 5 Nr 5 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "This also applies to temporary workers employed on a short-term basis, as well as to workers who have been made available by contractors for certain ordering, maintenance or harvesting work"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "For the crediting of the paid VAK"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "a breakdown of the wages is necessary, as far as it relates to the uses contained in the initial value (\u00a7 13a Abs 4 EStG) and to the uses not contained therein"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "the activities of other people (relatives, third parties) in the company or no or obviously incorrect information on the part of the work attributable to special uses, the (physical) work or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "the proportion of the work performed by the business owner, the relatives employed in the business and / or the remunerated workers, if applicable"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "with the assistance of the responsible official agricultural expert (ALS)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "The table in the Felsmann comment in Section C 219 on the average labor requirement for special branches of business can also serve as a guide to determine the share that is attributable to special uses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "The value of the work is to be calculated for owners of a part-time business in accordance with the order of 15 12 1982 S-2230 - 52 - St 113 and Section 130 Paragraph 4 Sentence 7 EStR"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "For examples of calculating the value of the work, see Annex 2223 Rent collected. Reference is made to Section 13a (6) sentence 2 EStG and Section 130a (7) EStR"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "The rent received also includes income from ground rent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Income from hunting leases is compensated by the basic amount as it relates to areas included in the initial value"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "224 Profits according to Section 13a Paragraph 8 EStG Reference is made to Section 13a Paragraph 8 EStG and Section 130a Paragraph 8 EStR"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "In addition, please note the following: Profits from operations that were not taken into account when determining the initial value are, for example,"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Additional profits from the sale of breeding cattle and other particularly valuable animals (see Section 2241), profits from renting rooms to holiday guests and camping sites (ESt-Kartei NW \u00a7\u00a7 13 13a EStG A No. 82), interest income, insofar as the capital claim is attributable to the business assets is, profits from riding schools and rental of own horses, insofar as it concerns income from agriculture and forestry, profits from secondary employment, profits from investments that belong to the agricultural and forestry business assets, profits from the keeping and care of retired animals, profits from the rearing of animals in a wage system"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Profits from the cross-company use of machines, which are achieved in the context of agriculture and forestry, are not to be recorded according to Section 13a (8) No. 3 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "You have already been paid for by applying the basic amount (ESt-Kartei NW \u00a7\u00a7 13 13a EStG A Nr 103)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "The profits (additional profits) according to \u00a7 13a Paragraph 8 EStG are basically to be determined by comparing the operating income and operating expenses (\u00a7 4 Paragraph 3 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "If no records are available, the profits (additional profits) are to be estimated according to the principles of Section 4 Paragraph 1 EStG (Section 130a Paragraph 8 Sentences 8 - 11 EStR)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "When estimating the profits (additional profits) from sales of breeding cattle and other particularly valuable animals as well as from vegetable growing and intensive fruit growing in the context of horticultural use, the following guidelines can serve as a guide"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Their application must not lead to an obviously incorrect taxation (see BFH judgment of 16 12 1965 BStBl 1966 III p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "193)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "2241 Sales of breeding cattle and other valuable animals As additional profit from the sale of breeding cattle and other particularly valuable animals, 80 per cent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "the amount by which the individual sales proceeds including sales tax exceed the following starting values \u200b\u200b(normal prices): Breeding bulls 2600 DMBreeding cows2200 DMBreeding cattle2000 DMBreeding boars and sows700 DMBreeding and riding horses3000 DMWages for paid workers, insurance and sales costs, etc."}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": ") are taken into account in the level of these initial values, so they cannot be deducted separately"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "The same procedure is then to be followed if above-average prices are obtained for breeding animals other than those specified or for other valuable animals"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "The initial value to be used in these cases results from the tax production costs of the animal species in question plus an assumed profit surcharge of 20% included in the initial value for the area under normal animal husbandry"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "2242 Vegetable growing (horticultural use) To distinguish vegetable growing (horticultural use) from vegetable growing within the framework of agricultural use, I refer to Sections 108, Paragraph 2 and 607, Paragraph 1, No. 1 BewRL 1964.If vegetable growing is included in agricultural use, there is a surcharge according to \u00a7 13a Paragraph 8 of the Income Tax Act not applicable"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Vegetables are only grown in the context of agricultural use if headed cabbage (white, red and savoy cabbage), picking peas and picking beans are grown exclusively using agricultural cultivation methods as part of agricultural crop rotation as the main crop"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "On the other hand, if the types of cabbage and / or peas or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Do not alternate beans with other agricultural crops such as"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Wheat, rye, barley, oats or beets, but one after the other or alternately with the same or different types of vegetables (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Endive, lettuce, lamb's lettuce, spinach, carrots, celery, beetroot, onions, radishes, leeks, tomatoes, kohlrabi, cucumbers, etc."}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": ") cultivated, the cultivation is no longer part of the agricultural crop rotation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "It is then rather about vegetable growing (horticultural use)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "In the case of vegetable growing (horticultural use), income fluctuates between DM 15,000 and DM 80,000 per hectare"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "You are dependent on z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "of soil quality, irrigation possibilities, under glass areas, number of harvests"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "The net profit can be 30 to 65 BC"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "of revenues are estimated"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "The profit is influenced by the type of marketing (auction in the wholesale market, sale on the farm, sale on the weekly market) and the wage expenditure"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "In the case of vegetable growing without roofed growing areas or with roofed growing areas up to 3%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "of the total vegetable growing area, the profit can also be estimated based on the number of unpaid family workers (FAK) fully employed in vegetable growing as follows: For a vegetable growing area - up to 2 ha 16,000 DM / FAK - from 2 to 4 ha 22,000 DM / FAK - over 4 ha38000 DM / FAK This estimation method is particularly suitable for cases in which the operating income has not been specified or has obviously been incomplete"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "A correct estimate in individual cases is i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "only possible in close cooperation with the ALS"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "2243 Fruit growing (horticultural use) The income fluctuates i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "between 15,000 and 35,000 DM per hectare"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "They depend on the type of fruit, the types of fruit, the age structure of the orchard, the quality of the soil and the climate"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Special natural events such as"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Late frosts can lead to lower income"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "The net profit can be 30 to 50 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "of revenues are estimated"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "The profit is influenced by the type of marketing (auction in the wholesale market, sale from the farm, sale at the weekly market) and the wage expenditure"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "No. 2242 last paragraph applies accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "225 Value in use of the apartment The apartment i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7 13a Paragraph 7 EStG includes the buildings and parts of buildings, insofar as they serve the owner of the business, the family members belonging to his household and the retirees for residential purposes (\u00a7 34 Paragraph 3 BewG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "This also applies if the right of residence of the senior citizen is secured in rem; the value in use is to be recorded in the amount of one eighteenth of the flat value specifically shown in the unit value in the income from agriculture and forestry and to be taken into account in the corresponding amount as a permanent burden according to \u00a7 10 para. 1 no 1983 Federal Tax Gazette 1984 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "226 Lease interest paid, interest on debt, ongoing charges Reference is made to Section 13a (3) sentence 2 EStG and Section 130a (9) EStR"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Interest subsidies from public funds reduce the deductible debt interest"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "227 Other additions and reductions"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "The following can be considered: additions and deductions according to \u00a7 6c EStG, increased deductions for residential buildings according to \u00a7 7b EStG i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "V with \u00a7 52 EStDV, tax relief according to \u00a7 78 EStDV With increased deductions according to \u00a7 7b EStG it should be noted that the loss clause of \u00a7 7a Abs 6 EStG a"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "no longer applies for financial years beginning after December 31, 1979 (Section 52 (21) EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "However, the tax relief according to \u00a7 78 EStDV may still not lead to a loss from agriculture and forestry (see \u00a7 78 Paragraph 3 EStDV)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "The other increased deductions according to \u00a7 7d EStG, \u00a7\u00a7 82a, 82g, and 82i EStDV and according to the Protective Building Act cannot be taken into account when determining profits according to \u00a7 13a Paragraphs 2 to 7 EStG because the average rates mean the depreciation and thus also the other The higher deductions occurring are generally compensated (see BFH judgment of 07 06 1984 BStBl 1984 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "663)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "However, if an asset is used in a part of the business whose full income is to be recorded in accordance with Section 13a (8) EStG, increased deductions can also be taken into account when determining the profit"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "3 Determination of the profit from agriculture and forestry by comparing the operating income with the operating expenses (Section 4 Paragraph 3 EStG) 31 Scope of application Reference is made to Section 127 Paragraph 3 EStR"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "32 Profit determination Refer to section 17 EStR and the following: 321 Average livestock values \u200b\u200bThe average rating (section 125 EStR) permitted for bookkeeping farmers and foresters can also be used under certain conditions when determining profits in accordance with Section 4 (3) EStR"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Otherwise, reference is made to Sect. 431"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "322 Value in use of the apartment To determine the value in use of the apartment, reference is made to the ESt card index NW \u00a7\u00a7 13 13a EStG A No. 100"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "According to this, the value in use is to be measured according to the circumstances of the individual case, even for farmers and foresters"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "With regard to the value in use of the apartment for elderly people, the BFH judgment of 28 07 1983 (BStBl 1984 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "97) must be observed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "According to this, the value in use is to be assigned to the owner even in the case of real security and to be taken into account in the corresponding amount as a permanent burden in accordance with Section 10 (1) No. 1a EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "4 Determination of the profit from agriculture and forestry through bookkeeping (Section 4 Paragraph 1 EStG) 41 Scope of application On Section 127 Paragraph 1 EStR and on No. 5 of the introductory letter of 27 03 1981 a"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": ", being point out"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Cattle surcharges are included in the determination of the economic value limit in accordance with Section 141 Paragraph 1 No. 3 AO"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "to be taken into account even if they have not yet been the subject of a value update according to \u00a7\u00a7 41 i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "V with 22 para 1 no 1 BewG have been made"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "42 Opening balance sheets To check the opening balance sheets when changing over to the comparison of business assets, reference is made to the order of 12 01 1984 S-2230 - 53 - St 113"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "43 Bookkeeping On section 13 EStR and the BMF letter of 15 12 1981 (BStBl I S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "878) is pointed out"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "44 Determination of profit 441 Average livestock values \u200b\u200bReference is made to section 125 EStR"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "The applicable cattle average values \u200b\u200bresult from the ESt-Kartei NW \u00a7\u00a7 13 13a EStG A No. 20 For the evaluation of horses from the 1980/81 business year onwards, reference is made to the order of 17 071981 S-2132 a - 1 - St 111"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "442 Value in use of the apartment Section 322 applies accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "5 Estimation of the profit for farmers and foresters whose profit cannot be determined according to average rates51 General For farmers and foresters who are obliged to keep accounts but do not keep proper books, the profit is to be estimated in individual cases according to \u00a7 162 AO"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "The same applies to those farmers and foresters who are neither obliged to keep accounts nor meet the requirements of Section 13a Paragraph 1 No. 2 and 3 EStG if they do not keep books within the meaning of Section 4 Paragraph 1 EStG and also the operating income and - have not recorded expenditures within the meaning of Section 4 Paragraph 3 EStG (Section 127 Paragraph 2 - 4 EStR)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "The estimate has - with the exception of the in Section 127 Paragraph 4 S."}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "6, second half-sentence of the EStR - to be carried out in accordance with the principles of Section 4 (1) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "When making the estimate, all circumstances that are important for the estimate must be taken into account (Section 162 (1) sentence 2 AO)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "The aim of the estimate must be to determine the profit actually achieved"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "The uncertainties inherent in an estimate are, however, at the expense of the taxpayer, who himself gave cause for the estimate by neglecting his tax cooperation obligations"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Which estimation method is to be used in each individual case is left to the discretion of the tax office"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "When estimating the profit, in cases in which there is a bookkeeping obligation, the investment must always be made, and in the other cases where the basis for the estimation is not sufficiently reliable, subject to review (Section 164 AO)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "The following explanatory text must be included in the notification or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "to be attached as an attachment: \"The profit from agriculture and forestry for the financial year 19"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "/ 19th"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "was estimated according to \u00a7 162 AO because you did not declare your winnings or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "because you declared a profit that was not determined by bookkeeping, although you are obliged to keep the books"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "If you actually achieved a higher profit than the estimated, the tax would have been set too low"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "In this case, there may be tax evasion or a frivolous tax reduction"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "However, you can then by declaring the actual profit under the further requirements of \u00a7\u00a7 371 378 Paragraph 3 AO criminal or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Obtain no fines"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Furthermore, I would like to point out that failure to comply with the accounting obligation can already result in a tax risk"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "\"52 Estimate of the profit according to standard rates If in individual cases an estimation method tailored to the particular operational conditions is not to be preferred, or there are no circumstances particularly influencing the operating result, such as"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Seed propagation or field vegetable cultivation exist or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "have been determined in the course of a previous tax audit and accounting results of comparable companies or empirical records are not available, the profit is to be estimated according to the principles of \u00a7 4 Paragraph 1 EStG as follows: Starting amount (Section 521) Lease income (Section 522) Surcharges for not including the starting amount paid for profits or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Additional profits (Sect. 523) Value in use of the apartment (Sect. 524)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Wage expenses (Section 525)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Lease expenses, debt interest, permanent burdens (Sect. 526)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Other surcharges and reductions (Section 527) = profit for the financial year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "The guideline rates listed below are intended as a guide for an accurate estimate of the profit (Section 127, Paragraph 2, p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "2 EStR)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "At the same time, a reduction in the estimated profit due to objections to individual points in the valuation process is generally out of the question because special circumstances in an individual branch of the business do not allow any conclusions to be drawn about the profit of the entire business"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "The application of the standard rates must not lead to an obviously incorrect taxation (see BFH judgment of 16 12 1965 BStBl 1966 III p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "193)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "In detail, the following should be taken into account when estimating profits according to standard rates: 521 Starting amount The starting amount per hectare of usable agricultural area (UAA) for the 1983/1984 financial year is: for pasture farming (grassland share 71 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "and more of the LN) 1400 DM for mixed farms (grassland share 31 to 70 per cent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "der LN) with a minced fruit content of less than 15%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "the LN1400 DM15 v"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "and more than the LN1500 DM"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "the LN and is in it a sugar beet content of more than 20%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "of the LN, the starting amount increases to DM 2,200"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "of the LN, are each started 5 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Additional portion of root crops to be added to the above starting amounts for every 200 DM"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "der LN) with a root crop content of a) less than 15%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "the LN1400 DMb) 15 v"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "and more of LN1800 DMc) No. 2 c) and 2 d) apply accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "In the case of dairy cow husbandry, the starting amounts (No. 1 - 3) are to be increased according to the average dairy cow herd of the farm as follows: a) less than 05 cows / ha LN200 DMb) 05 to less than 1 cows / ha LN300 DMc) 1 and more cows / ha LN400 DM"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Only the pure agricultural production areas belong to the agricultural use"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Areas for buildings, courtyards, paths, ditches, field borders, water, land, quarries, sand pits, etc."}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Areas are therefore not considered"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Areas for house gardens are also not included"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Otherwise, Section 124a (3) EStR applies accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "For the calculation of the relevant root crop, grassland or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Sugar beet share depends on the size of these shares in the respective marketing year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "The areas under cultivation of root crops do not include those areas on which root crops are only grown as catch crops or as catch crops"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Only those in Paragraph"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "5232 listed meadows and pastures; the other crops mentioned there (fodder plants) belong to field forage cultivation, the areas of which belong to the field"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "With regard to the increase in the starting amounts by a security surcharge of up to a maximum of 30% to be made in cases of repeated profit estimates from the 1983/1984 financial year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "reference is made to the order of 5 4 1983 S-2150 a - 2 - St 113"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "522 Lease income Lease income, ground rent and hunting leases, reduced by proportionate operating expenses, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Property taxes are to be added to the starting amount if they are included in income from agriculture and forestry"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "This is the case when the leased or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Hereditary assets belong to the lessor's agricultural and forestry business assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "523 Surcharges for winnings or winnings not settled with the starting amount"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "All profits from sustainable or one-off operating income that are not included in the starting amount are to be added to the starting amount"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Such surcharges come z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Consideration for additional profits from sales of breeding cattle and other particularly valuable animals, profits from abnormal animal husbandry, additional profits from special crops, profits from other special branches of business, profits from the removal and sale of land (see \"Sale / removal of land\" on page 2 of the annex L)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "The surcharges are generally to be determined by comparing the operating income and operating expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "If no records are available, the profits (additional profits) are to be estimated"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "The following guidelines can serve as a guide: 5231 Sales of breeding cattle and other particularly valuable animals Section 2241 applies accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "5232 Abnormal animal husbandry Profits from animal breeding and husbandry are settled with the starting amount (Section 521), provided that the average normal animal population is not exceeded"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "As animal husbandry paid for with the starting amount, for the area of \u200b\u200bthe regional tax office in Cologne, other companies for the first 20 ha LN22 VE / ha14 VE / ha for the next 10 ha LN 16 VE / ha08 VE / haf for the next 20 ha LN 15 VE / ha07 VE / ha over 50 ha of LN, a maximum of 90 VE50 VE The animal husbandry in VE, which is covered with the starting amount, can also be found in the overview attached as Annex 1"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Forage farms are farms where the forage area is 60 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "and more of the usable agricultural area without courtyard and building space, etc."}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "matters"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "In this context, the forage area includes: Meadows (incl"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Tree meadows, litter meadows), cattle pastures and fields, as well as the cultivation areas for clover in pure seed and mixed cultivation, clover grass, alfalfa, seradella, sainfin, green corn, vetches, sweet lupins and all other forage plants"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "When calculating the number of animals and converting them into livestock units, Section 124a, Paragraph 2 of the Income Tax Regulations must be used"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "The average herds (lines 79 to 85 of Appendix L) and the animals produced (lines 86 to 92 of Appendix L) are to be summarized"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Care must be taken that no animals are recorded twice"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "For the excess stock remaining after the normal stock has been taken into account, the profit for the 1983/1984 financial year is to be set as a profit: as a rule, if the stock is kept exclusively (90 per cent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "and more) of 450 DM / VE fattening poultry 200 DM / VE hens 300 DM / VE fattening pigs 350 DM / VE wages are not taken into account here, so they can still be deducted"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "5233 Field vegetable cultivation (agricultural use) Field vegetable cultivation is understood to mean the cultivation of vegetables according to agricultural cultivation methods within the framework of agricultural crop rotation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "A distinction must be made between field vegetable cultivation in annual cultivation and field vegetable cultivation as a replica"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "The additional profit not settled with the starting amount (Section 521) is to be set for the 1983/1984 financial year: For field vegetable growing in annual cultivation: 7,000 DM per hectare minus the amount per hectare / lan included in the starting amount for this area, as a replica: 5,000 DM per hectare ( without reduction)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "It is up to the taxpayer to provide evidence of the actual proceeds from field vegetable growing"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "In these cases, a discount of 25 per cent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "be acknowledged"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "The remaining amount is only to be reduced in the case of field vegetable cultivation in annual cultivation by the amount per hectare / UI set in the starting amount for this area"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "The above standard rates do not take into account wages and can therefore be deducted separately"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "5234 Vegetable growing (horticultural use) Section 2242 applies accordingly to the determination of profit"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "As a surcharge on the starting amount, however, only the additional profit, i.e."}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "the profit reduced by the pro-rata starting amount applied in the individual case"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "5235 Fruit growing (horticultural use) Section 2243 applies accordingly to the determination of profit"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "As a surcharge on the starting amount, however, only the additional profit, i.e."}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "the profit reduced by the pro-rata starting amount applied in the individual case"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "524 Value in use of the apartment, Section 322 applies accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "When estimating the profit, the gross value in use must always be applied, because the expenses associated with the apartment - with the exception of interest on debt (Section 526) and the increased deductions (Section 527) - are taken into account when determining the starting amounts (Section 521) and are thus compensated are"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "525 Wage expenses The starting amount (Section 521) is based on the assumption that the company is managed exclusively with unpaid workers"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Wage expenses are therefore to be deducted from the starting amount insofar as they relate to the profits settled with the starting amount"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "The treatment of wage expenses incurred with profits or income not paid for in the starting amount"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Additional profits (see Sect. 523) result from the respective surcharge regulations (see Sections 5231 to 5235)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "For the distribution of wage expenses required in individual cases, Section 222 Nos"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "2 and 3 apply accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "The wage expenses to be deducted also include the expenses for short-term temporary workers as well as for the workers who are"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Contractors have been made available for certain ordering, maintenance or harvesting work"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "If wage expenses in connection with machine expenses are invoiced in one sum by contractors, there are generally no concerns that the proportionate wage expenses to be taken into account at 25%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "appreciate"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "If wage expenses cannot be proven, an estimate e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "possible according to documents from comparable companies"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Because of the need to notify the income tax office in such cases, please refer to section 62 lit."}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "c) pointed out"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "526 Lease expenses, debt interest, permanent charges Such expenses can be deducted if they are operating expenses and have not already been taken into account when determining the surcharges according to Sect. 523"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "The lease payments then attributable to the profit settled with the starting amount are not fully deductible"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "The lease also covers expenses that are already included in the starting amount as operating expenses (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Property tax, apportionment of the Chamber of Agriculture, professional association contribution)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "The lease payments are therefore to be reduced by the amount contained therein, which is allotted to such expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "There are no concerns about reducing this amount to 15 per cent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "to estimate the rent payments"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "In special individual cases it may be justified to reduce the amount to 10 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "lower if excessive and no longer local rent is paid"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "527 Other surcharges and reductions 527 Allocation due to building depreciation in the case of profit estimation When calculating the starting amount, the deductions for wear and tear from the value of the business buildings are taken into account in accordance with \u00a7 7 EStG, because it is assumed that the business is managed by the owner himself"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Insofar as this depreciation is due to someone other than the manager of the business, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "the lessor in the case of leasing, are to be added to the initial amount of the LN (Section 521) when estimating the profit: For buildings essentially erected before 11/1965: 10,000 DM per hectare of LN, for buildings mainly erected after December 31, 1964: 15,000 DM per hectare of LN"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "It is up to the tenant to prove the AfA in detail"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "5272 Increased reductions"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "increased deductions for residential buildings according to \u00a7 7b EStG and increased deductions according to \u00a7\u00a7 82a, 82g and 82i EStDV into consideration"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "These increased deductions are, however, by the depreciation already taken into account in the starting amount according to \u00a7 7 Abs 4 EStG in the amount of 2 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "to shorten"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "5273 Special depreciation according to \u00a7 76 EStDV Special depreciation according to \u00a7 76 EStDV can be deducted from the starting amount if the register is kept according to \u00a7 7a Paragraph 8 EStG (see order of 27 5 1981 S-2184 - 7 - St 111)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "In these cases, I ask you to request the directory and to attach a copy of the income tax file"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "After the expiry of the preferential period of three financial years, the starting amount must be increased by a surcharge when claiming the preferential treatment according to \u00a7 76 EStDV, since according to \u00a7 76 Paragraph 1 Clause 2 EStDV the residual value is the assessment basis for further deductions for wear and tear and by applying the starting amount otherwise too high depreciation amounts would be taken into account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "The surcharge for a financial year results from the sum of the special depreciation granted divided by the remaining useful life of the respective asset"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "The initial amount must be increased for the remaining period of use"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "In order to ensure that this surcharge is also taken into account in future assessments, the directory to be attached to the income tax file must be provided with a corresponding note"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "6 Other 61 Retirement benefits 612 The following values \u200b\u200bcan be used as a basis for non-cash retirement benefits for the 1983 full-time pension without individual proof: for meals, for an old-age divider, 2740 DM, for a married couple, 4930 DM, for heating and lighting, 570 DM"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "With regard to the value for heating and lighting, however, there are no concerns, requests from taxpayers to apply the pro rata, based on the energy bills or similar"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "the actual costs determined"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "613 If partial retirement benefits do not only consist of benefits in kind and in kind due to farm handover agreements between parents and children, it must be checked in each individual case whether the individual partial benefits are life annuities or permanent burdens (recurring payments)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Section 167 (1) no.2 letter c) EStR 1981 is based on the BFH judgment of 28 July 1983 (BStBl 1984 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "97) outdated"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Because of the transitional regulation for existing retirement contracts, reference is made to the decree of FinMin NW of 18 10 1984 S-2221 - 109 - V B 2 with a ruling of 26 10 1984 S-2221 - 28 - St 113"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "62 Control notifications Except in the usual cases (control notifications for the purposes of the Bp, the recording of taxable transactions with other taxpayers, inheritance tax), control notifications are to be prepared in the following cases in particular: The assessment body responsible in each individual case is to be informed of the taxpayer's or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "to disclose circumstances arising from the files that may affect the level of the fixed unit values \u200b\u200b(e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Change in areas for special use, changes in animal populations - see also order of 4 10 1977 S-3122 - 4 - St 241)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Information that may be of importance for an award according to \u00a7 41 BewG is summarized on page 4 of Annex L."}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "I therefore ask in all cases in which the livestock declared in Annex L obviously exceeds or exceeds the animal population customary in the area"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "in which, for other reasons, a surcharge according to \u00a7 41 BewG may be considered, the assessment body can be informed by sending a copy of page 4 of Annex L."}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Are access or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Leases known, so the lessor or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Inform the leaseholder of the competent assessment office"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "The same applies to the transfer of use free of charge"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "This can be done in accordance with No. 3 of the order of 4 2 1981 S-2230 - 46 - St 111"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "For the rest, I ask you to ensure that the taxpayers on page 2 of Annex L the address of the lessee / lessor, etc."}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "specify exactly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "In particular, cases without signal \"A\", in which wage expenses are claimed, and cases with significant wage expenses are to be reported to the responsible income tax office for examination by the income tax field audit"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "This also applies if wage expenses are set at an estimated amount when determining the profit (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Section 525 Paragraph 4)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "63 Standard value notifications Unit value notifications for agricultural and forestry assets must always be evaluated promptly, particularly because of the possible effects on the way in which the taxpayer's profit is determined"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "64 Consultation of the valuation files when carrying out the assessment In particular when determining profits in accordance with Section 13a of the Income Tax Act (EStG) and in valuation cases, I ask that you refer to the assessment files for the assessment and review of the values \u200b\u200bto be applied in the individual case when calculating profits"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "The plants were not included"}, {"meta": {"name": "0049885.xml"}, "text": "Accounting income tax / wage tax / church tax North Rhine-Westphalia agriculture"}]